
// This Hyperlambda code snippet converts the value of the [threshold] node within the [.arguments] node to a double type and then sets this converted value back to the [threshold] node. The [set-value] slot is used to assign the converted value, while the [convert] slot changes the type of the [threshold] node's value to double.
set-value:x:@.arguments/*/threshold
   convert:x:@.arguments/*/threshold
      type:double
